{"parse":{"title":"Indirectly controlled variable","pageid":1473,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>5-2-160</b>\n</p><p><span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"7fc56270e7a70fa81a5935b72eacbe29\">A</span> variable which does not originate a feedback signal, but which is related to, and influenced by, the directly controlled variable.\n</p><p><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:Ch5_Fig2.jpg\" class=\"mw-file-description\"><img src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/thumb/f/fb/Ch5_Fig2.jpg/400px-Ch5_Fig2.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"400\" height=\"220\" class=\"mw-file-element\" srcset=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/thumb/f/fb/Ch5_Fig2.jpg/600px-Ch5_Fig2.jpg 1.5x, /wiki/dictionary/images/thumb/f/fb/Ch5_Fig2.jpg/800px-Ch5_Fig2.jpg 2x\"></a></span>\n</p><p>Figure 2 - Block diagram of automatic control system (5-2-045) incorporating a closed loop (5-2-080)\n</p><p>Reference: ANSI\n</p><p><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<i>Please note that this is the term as it stands in the original <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\">IALA</span> Dictionary edition (1970-1989)</i>\n<br>\n</p>\n<div class=\"LanguageLinks\">\n<table width=\"100%\">\n<tbody><tr valign=\"top\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF\">\n<td style=\"width: 25px; padding-left: 0em; border-right: 1px solid #aaaaaa;border-left: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-top: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-bottom: 1px solid #EEF3E2;\"><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:25px-Geographylogo.png\" class=\"mw-file-description\" title=\"Languages\"><img alt=\"Languages\" src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/8/82/25px-Geographylogo.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" class=\"mw-file-element\"></a></span></td>\n<td style=\"padding: 1px 1em 0; background: #EEF3E2;\">\n<p><b><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">English</a></b>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n</p>\n</td></tr></tb